On Mon, Feb 15, 2010 at 9:52 PM, Todd Olson <todd.olson(-at-)charter.net> wrote:

> Hello Fellow Bus Pilots,
>
> It is that time again for the annual pilgrimage of Bus Pilots to converge
> upon Pokagon State Park in Angola, IN. Buses and their frozen pilots will
> be
> traversing the snow and ice covered roads in search of what they long for;
> a
> chance to toot the horn, smell the exhaust from their magnesium block
> engines and to camp with good friends. Heater boxes are for sissies when it
> comes to this adventurous winter campout. Those Bus Pilots sporting J
> pipes, a snowmobile suit and ice scraper in one hand to use while driving
> earn major style points with this crowd.
>
>
>
> As the winter seems to drag on to long and our need to disappear in our
> buses seem to become greater, then shake the winter blues and join us for
> this fun family (and dog) friendly campout. There will be lots to eat. Many
> people bring crock pots and plug them in with soups and chilies to be
> enjoyed by all. At the campground there will be a roaring bon fire, heated
> bathrooms, electricity for heaters and a toboggan run that is < mile long
> and goes 40 MPH. (faster then many of our buses!) We will be giving away a
> Phoenix Society for Burn Survivors Stadium Blanket that rolls up into a
> holder to the winner of the Cozy Bus Award. Average temps for Angola,
> Indiana in February is a high of 33 and a low of 16.
>
>
>
> Everyone will be arriving around 12:30 -1:00PM at Campground #3 on Saturday
> 2/27.
>
>
>
> So lets hear from you. Who is up for the challenge of a winter bus
> campout??
>
>
>
